            <section>
               <id root="75503c71-c167-4d5e-bde0-bd8a09f756ba"/>
               <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
               <title>DIRECTIONS</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Soak a cotton-tipped applicator or a pledget of cotton with Hemo-Stat. Apply to bleeding area with pressure until hemorrhage is arrested.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20100513"/>
               <component>
                  <section>
                     <id root="e3c96d6d-cfca-41a9-a14f-1440d5038e46"/>
                     <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
                     <title>Note</title>
                     <text>
                        <paragraph>Should a small dark coagulum appear, flush it away with water. This will have no effect on the hemostatic action.</paragraph>
                        <paragraph>Hemo-Stat Solution contains 25% Aluminum Chloride in an aqueous vehicle. It contains no epinephrine.</paragraph>
                     </text>
                     <effectiveTime value="20100513"/>
                  </section>
               </component>
            </section>
